update public.lessons l set enhancements = $ench${"industryStory":"Every test repeated the same login steps in beforeEach, cluttering the specs. A custom loggedInPage fixture handed each test an authenticated page — shorter tests, setup in one place, torn down automatically.","davidTip":"Use fixtures for reusable state (a logged-in page, seeded data) and set baseURL in config so tests use relative paths. Enable retries in CI only — locally you want to see flakiness, not mask it.","miniChallenge":"Add a baseURL to your config and switch a test to a relative path; then sketch a simple custom fixture.","modelAnswer":"## Example\nuse: { baseURL: 'https://app.example.com' } → page.goto('/login'). Fixture: loggedInPage logs in once and hands tests an authenticated page, so each test skips repeated setup.","resourcePreview":{"name":"Fixtures & Hooks Guide","purpose":"Set up and tear down cleanly with fixtures and hooks.","whenToUse":"Use it when extracting shared setup.","formats":["PDF","DOCX"]}}$ench$::jsonb
